                                                                     -*-Text-*-

Google userspace coredumper library

Version 1.4 (2026-03-17)

  New Features:

  > Generate an NT_FILE note into the generated core file.
    GDB reads this note and, up to version GDB 17.1, will only retrieve
    shared libraries from debuginfod if this note exists.

  > Support generating core files on 64bit ARM systems.

  > Dump the first page of ELF executable/library mappings.
    Change from: Romain Geissler <romain.geissler@amadeus.com>

  Bug fixes:
  * Cope with the removal of sys/sysctl.h in recent glibc/kernel.
    Change from: Romain Geissler <romain.geissler@amadeus.com>
  * Fix child stack alignment assembly code.
    Change from: Zsolt Parragi <zsolt.parragi@cancellar.hu>
  * Align initial stack pointer correctly.
    Change from: DoctorNoobingstoneIPresume <adder.thief@gmail.com>

  Tests:
  * Enhance the unittest to generate more information on failure.
  * Support alternative readelf and gdb via environment variables.

  Other:
  * Support clangd as an LSP server
  * Some code cleanup and simplification.


Version 1.3.1 (2017-12-16)

  New Features:

  > Add support for a callback invoked after all threads are paused.


Version 1.3 (2017-05-20)

  Bug fixes:
  * Do not try to read vvar memory segments marked VM_DONTDUMP
  * Do not use sizeof(<VLA>) as it generates the wrong value.
    Change from: Max Akhmedov <zlobober@users.noreply.github.com>
  * Support executables built with RELRO.
    Change from: Romain Geissler <romain.geissler@amadeus.com>
  * Allow coredumping on systems with YAMA ptrace protection.
    Change by: Happy Ox


Versions 1.0 (2007-02-15) through 1.2.1 (2008-04-04)

  > These versions provided by Google.
  > See the ChangeLog file
